            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Length and Configuration Considerations: CIPP lining works for virtually any residential sewer line length from 20-foot sections to 200+ foot main lines, with longer runs often more cost-effective due to mobilization being a smaller percentage of total cost. Pipe configuration has minimal impact: multiple bends and turns are easily handled (the flexible liner conforms to any configuration), diameter changes can be accommodated with custom liner fabrication, lateral connections are reinstated using robotic cutting equipment, and vertical drops or rises pose no problems. The main limitation is access—we need to be able to insert the liner and reach the entire section requiring repair. Our camera inspection evaluates your specific pipe configuration and confirms trenchless suitability before providing quotes."
